Tavatron:

Dinobot was kicking up a considerable amount of dirt and dust before he 
finally settled down and allowed Tavatron to get close enough to place a 
tentative hand on the small furball. Tavatron could tell by Dinobot's stance 
that whatever this creature was he was prepared to kill it if necessary. She 
shouldn't have laughed, and was prepared to tell Dinobot so if he would just 
calm down long enough to let her attempt the removal of the small bundle of 
black fur:

"I apologize, I shouldn't have laughed."

Tavatron peered closely at the small creature, her nose was centimeters from 
it's own when it swipped at her. Tavatron jumped back and whimpered softly. 
It wasn't a matter of pride, well, perhaps it was, but most 'bots knew that 
the nose was one of the most sensitive parts of a creature, especially 
wolves.

She stood a few feet away, rubbing her snout and contemplating her next 
move. Whatever that thing was it definitely wasn't something she wanted to 
touch again anytime soon. Tavatron removed her staff from subspace and spun 
it once, taking careful aim at the small creature. Perhaps she could knock 
it off with the blunt end of her staff:

"Hold still, I'm going to try and hit it."
